  "misconception": {
    "claim": "Rotational motion needs its own special set of equations to memorize.",
    "refuted_by": "The rotational kinematics equations *are* the straight-line ones with angular symbols: $x\\to\\theta$, $v\\to\\omega$, $a\\to\\alpha$. They come from the same two integrations of a constant acceleration — the slope of the $\\omega$–$t$ line is $\\alpha$, and the area under it is $\\Delta\\theta$. Learn one set, relabel, and you have the other."
